        <!-- What is Bitcoin Cloud Mining -->
        <article class="content-card fade-in" id="what-is">
            <h2>What Is Bitcoin Cloud Mining?</h2>
            <p>Bitcoin cloud mining represents the professionalization and democratization of cryptocurrency mining. In 2026, it has evolved into a sophisticated industry where individual investors can access enterprise-level mining infrastructure without the complexities of hardware ownership.</p>
            
            <p>When you participate in cloud mining, you're purchasing a contractual right to a specific amount of computational power within a large-scale mining operation. These facilities use the latest ASIC miners (Application-Specific Integrated Circuits) optimized for Bitcoin mining, operating 24/7 in locations with affordable electricity and optimal cooling conditions.</p>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Key Concept: Hashrate</h4>
                <p>Hashrate measures computational power in terahashes per second (TH/s). Your cloud mining contract specifies how much hashrate you control. More hashrate = greater share of mining rewards. In 2026, modern mining facilities operate at petahash (PH/s) and exahash (EH/s) levels, providing unprecedented efficiency.</p>
            </div>
            
            <h3>How Investors Profit from Cloud Mining</h3>
            <p>Cloud mining generates profit through a simple yet powerful model: <strong>You earn Bitcoin proportionate to your contributed hashrate.</strong> When the mining pool successfully validates Bitcoin transactions and mines new blocks, rewards are distributed daily based on your contract's computational power allocation.</p>
        </article>

        <!-- How It Works - Step by Step -->
        <article class="content-card fade-in" id="how-works">
            <h2>How Bitcoin Cloud Mining Works (Step by Step)</h2>
            
            <ol class="step-list">
                <li>
                    <strong>Enterprise Mining Infrastructure</strong>
                    <p>Professional providers operate industrial mining farms with thousands of ASIC miners in strategic locations. These facilities leverage renewable energy sources, low-cost electricity regions, and advanced cooling systems for optimal efficiency.</p>
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <strong>Hashrate Contract Selection</strong>
                    <p>You select a mining plan corresponding to specific computational power (e.g., 100 TH/s, 500 TH/s). This purchase gives you rights to that hashrate for the contract duration (typically 12-36 months in 2026).</p>
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <strong>Mining Pool Integration</strong>
                    <p>Your allocated hashrate joins a mining pool combining power with thousands of other miners. Pooling increases reward frequency and stability compared to solo mining.</p>
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <strong>Continuous Blockchain Processing</strong>
                    <p>Your computational power works 24/7 to validate Bitcoin transactions, secure the network, and solve cryptographic puzzles that generate new Bitcoin through block rewards.</p>
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <strong>Daily Bitcoin Distribution</strong>
                    <p>When the mining pool successfully mines a block, rewards (currently 3.125 BTC + transaction fees after 2024 halving) are distributed proportionally based on each participant's contributed hashrate. Earnings are calculated and credited daily.</p>
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <strong>Automatic Portfolio Growth</strong>
                    <p>Your earned Bitcoin automatically accumulates in your account. Most platforms offer flexible options: withdraw to personal wallets, reinvest in additional hashrate, or convert to fiat currency.</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </article>

        <!-- How Users Earn Money -->
        <article class="content-card fade-in" id="earnings">
            <h2>How Investors Earn Bitcoin from Cloud Mining</h2>
            
            <p>Cloud mining generates earnings through a transparent mechanism where computational power directly translates to Bitcoin rewards:</p>
            
            <div class="earning-steps">
                <div class="earning-step-card">
                    <div class="step-number">1</div>
                    <h3>Hashrate Allocation</h3>
                    <p>Your contract secures specific computational power within the mining pool's total capacity</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="earning-step-card">
                    <div class="step-number">2</div>
                    <h3>Continuous Mining</h3>
                    <p>Your hashrate works 24/7 to validate transactions and compete for block rewards</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="earning-step-card">
                    <div class="step-number">3</div>
                    <h3>Reward Generation</h3>
                    <p>The pool earns Bitcoin through block rewards (3.125 BTC per block in 2026) and transaction fees</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="earning-step-card">
                    <div class="step-number">4</div>
                    <h3>Proportional Distribution</h3>
                    <p>You receive daily BTC payments proportional to your hashrate contribution percentage</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Real-World Earnings Mechanism (2026 Example)</h3>
            <p>Imagine you purchase 500 TH/s of mining power in a pool operating at 50,000 TH/s total capacity. You own 1% of the pool's hashrate. When the pool mines a block worth 3.125 BTC, your share would be 0.03125 BTC (approximately 1% of the reward).</p>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Earnings Optimization in 2026</h4>
                <p>Professional cloud mining providers optimize earnings through: Strategic facility locations with renewable energy, Latest-generation ASIC miners (200+ TH/s efficiency), Smart pool switching algorithms, and Regular hardware upgrades. These optimizations maximize your return on hashrate investment.</p>
            </div>
        </article>

