        <!-- Glossary Section -->
        <section class="glossary-section fade-in" id="glossary">
            <h2>Bitcoin Cloud Mining Terminology (2026 Edition)</h2>
            <p>Understanding these essential terms will help you make informed decisions about cloud mining investments:</p>
            
            <div class="glossary-grid">
                <div class="glossary-term">
                    <div class="term-title">Hashrate (TH/s)</div>
                    <p>Computational power measurement. 1 TH/s = 1 trillion calculations per second. Determines your mining rewards share.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="glossary-term">
                    <div class="term-title">ASIC Miner</div>
                    <p>Application-Specific Integrated Circuit - specialized hardware designed exclusively for Bitcoin mining with maximum efficiency.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="glossary-term">
                    <div class="term-title">Mining Pool</div>
                    <p>Group of miners combining computational power to increase block discovery frequency and reward consistency.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="glossary-term">
                    <div class="term-title">Block Reward</div>
                    <p>New Bitcoin created and awarded to miners for successfully validating a block (3.125 BTC in 2026).</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="glossary-term">
                    <div class="term-title">Network Difficulty</div>
                    <p>Automatically adjusts every 2 weeks based on total network hashrate. Higher difficulty requires more computational power.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="glossary-term">
                    <div class="term-title">Proof of Work</div>
                    <p>Bitcoin's consensus mechanism requiring computational work to validate transactions and secure the network.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <section class="faq-section fade-in">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (2026 Update)</h2>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <span>How do cloud mining earnings compare to buying Bitcoin directly?</span>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Cloud mining provides continuous Bitcoin accumulation regardless of price movements. While buying Bitcoin gives you immediate exposure at current prices, mining generates new Bitcoin over time through computational work. During periods of Bitcoin price appreciation, mining can potentially accumulate more BTC than an equivalent initial investment could purchase, though this depends on network difficulty and operational efficiency.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <span>What happens when my mining contract ends?</span>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>At contract expiration, your hashrate allocation ends. You retain all Bitcoin earned during the contract period. Most reputable providers offer contract renewal options with updated hardware based on current mining technology, or you can explore new mining plans reflecting 2026 market conditions and technological advancements.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <span>How transparent are cloud mining operations in 2026?</span>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Leading providers now offer unprecedented transparency: Live mining farm footage via 24/7 video streams, real-time hashrate monitoring dashboards, public wallet addresses for blockchain verification, regular audited operational reports, and detailed fee breakdowns. Always verify a provider's transparency measures before investing.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <span>Can I increase my mining power after starting?</span>
                    <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Yes, scalability is one of cloud mining's key advantages. Most platforms allow you to purchase additional hashrate at any time. This flexibility lets you start with a conservative investment and increase your computational power as you become comfortable with the process and as your investment strategy evolves.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
